# Custom Alert Rules System

Allow admins to define their own alert rules that the system evaluates automatically. For example: *"Alert me when a vehicle has driven 50km since its last brake change."*

## Architecture Overview

The system is built around a **Rule Engine** pattern:

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[Admin creates rule] --> B[AlertRule saved to MongoDB]
    B --> C[GET /api/dashboard/alerts evaluates all rules]
    C --> D[Matching vehicles generate alerts]
    D --> E[Alerts shown in Header bell + Notifications page]
```

### Design Decisions

**Condition Types** — Based on analyzing the Vehicle schema, the admin can monitor these data sources:

| Category | Field | Operators | Example |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Mileage Since Service** | `mileage_since_oil_change`, `mileage_since_tire_rotation`, `mileage_since_brake_check` | `>`, `>=` | *"Alert if mileage since brake check > 50 km"* |
| **Days Since Service** | `days_since_oil_change`, `days_since_tire_rotation`, `days_since_brake_check`, `days_since_general_inspection` | `>`, `>=` | *"Alert if days since oil change > 90"* |
| **Expiry Countdown** | `registration_expiry_days`, `insurance_expiry_days` | `<`, `<=` | *"Alert if registration expires within 30 days"* |
| **Vehicle Property** | `current_mileage`, `vehicle_age` | `>`, `>=`, `<`, `<=`, `=` | *"Alert if mileage > 200000"* |
| **Component Condition** | `battery_condition`, `brake_fluid_condition`, `coolant_condition`, `engine_belt_condition`, `distribution_chain_condition` | `=` | *"Alert if battery condition = poor"* |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The existing hardcoded alerts in [dashboard.controller.js](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/backend/controllers/dashboard.controller.js) will remain as **system defaults**. Custom rules are evaluated **in addition** to them.

