## Proposed Changes

### Backend

---

#### [NEW] [AlertRule.js](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/backend/models/AlertRule.js)

New Mongoose model:

```js
{
  name: String,           // "Brake Check Overdue"
  description: String,    // "Alert when vehicle exceeds 50km since last brake check"
  conditionField: String, // "mileage_since_brake_check"
  operator: String,       // ">"
  value: Number|String,   // 50
  severity: String,       // "warning" | "urgent" | "info"
  isActive: Boolean,      // true
  createdBy: ObjectId,    // ref: User
}
```

#### [MODIFY] [index.js](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/backend/models/index.js)

Export the new `AlertRule` model.

#### [NEW] [alertRule.controller.js](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/backend/controllers/alertRule.controller.js)

CRUD endpoints + a **rule evaluation engine** function that:
1. Fetches all active `AlertRule` documents.
2. For each rule, queries the Vehicle collection to find matches.
3. Returns generated alert objects.

#### [NEW] [alertRule.routes.js](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/backend/routes/alertRule.routes.js)

- `GET    /api/alert-rules` — List all rules
- `POST   /api/alert-rules` — Create rule (admin only)
- `PUT    /api/alert-rules/:id` — Update rule (admin only)
- `DELETE /api/alert-rules/:id` — Delete rule (admin only)

#### [MODIFY] [dashboard.controller.js](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/backend/controllers/dashboard.controller.js)

Modify [getAlerts](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/backend/controllers/dashboard.controller.js#366-477) to also call the rule evaluation engine and merge custom rule alerts with the existing hardcoded alerts.

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/backend/server.js)

Mount the new alert-rules routes.

